FORM Holdings Corp.


            
            FORM Holdings Corp. engages in the innovation, development, and monetization of intellectual property, as well as the commercialization and distribution of wire free power and rugged computing devices. It operates through the following segments: Intellectual Property, Fli Charge, and Group Mobile. The The Intellectual Property segment innovates, develops, and manages the company intellectual property. It consists of over 600 patents and patent applications covering telecom infrastructure, internet search, ad-insertion and mobile technologies. The Fli Charge segment designs, develops, licenses, manufactures and markets wire-free conductive power and charging solutions. The Group Mobile segment provides  rugged, mobile, and field-use computing products, serving customers worldwide. The company was founded by Jonathan Medved and David Goldfarb in January 9, 2006 and is headquartered in New York, NY.

            
